<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4ccba8b2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10497"><num value="10497">§ 10497.</num><heading> Reports</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A State or local law enforcement agency or organization that receives a grant under this subchapter shall submit to the Attorney General an annual report that includes—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4ccba8b3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10497/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> program descriptions;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4ccba8b4-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10497/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the number of staff employed to administer programs;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4ccba8b5-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10497/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the number of individuals who participated in programs; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4ccba8b6-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10497/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> an evaluation of the effectiveness of grant programs.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id4ccba8b7-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/351/tI/s2307">Pub. L. 90–351, title I, § 2307</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXI/s210201/a/3">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXI, § 210201(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2064">108 Stat. 2064</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
